title: Aapas Ki Baat
subTitle: Kajal and Anand's love story is cut short after Kajal's family disapproves of their relationship. Years later, fate brings them back into each other's lives, but all is not as it seems.

title: Tulsi
subTitle: Tulsi wants to marry Ganesh, but her father does not agree. Meanwhile, when the village matchmakers arrange for her marriage with Thakur Singh, she strives to marry the person of her choice.

title: Shiv Ganga
subTitle: When Kamdev attempts to provoke feelings of lust in Lord Shiva with the arrow of love, he faces a wrath that threatens his life.

title: Phool Aur Angaar
subTitle: A young man rescues a woman from being molested but gets accused of the heinous crime instead. Trying to apprehend the miscreants, he gets caught in a web of deception and lies.

title: Ek Hasina Do Diwane
subTitle: Best friends Amar and Prakash love Neetu, but she marries Amar against her father's wishes. Their different lifestyles create problems and Prakash makes things worse.

title: Kohram
subTitle: Colonel Balbir Singh Sodhi assumes a disguise to unveil the true colours of Veer Bhadra Singh, a corrupt minister. Soon, Major Ajit teams up with him to execute the mission.

title: Bhrashtachar
subTitle: Journalist Bhavani intends to expose and bring to justice a corrupt politician who pretends to be a social worker. However, she soon finds herself trapped in a web of conspiracies.

title: Ghar Ka Chiraag
subTitle: Kiran marries Kumar, believing her love, Ravi, to be dead. When Ravi returns years later, Kiran is forced to confront the painful secrets surrounding her past and her marriage.

title: Raeeszada
subTitle: When Sanjay, a policeman, arrests Jagannath, a gangster, his senior disagrees and frees the goon. Sanjay decides to resign and fight corruption on his own.

title: Mera Desh Mera Dharam
subTitle: Sajid, the son of an army officer, joins an armed freedom struggle in a bid to liberate the Bangladeshi populace from the oppressive Pakistani regime. However, his personal life faces turmoil.
